 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/single-number-iii/description/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2024-05-31&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given an integer array  &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt; , in which exactly two elements appear only once and all the other elements appear exactly twice. Find the two elements that appear only once. You can return the answer in &lt;strong&gt;any order&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must write an algorithm that runs in linear runtime complexity and uses only constant extra space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [1,2,1,3,2,5]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [3,5]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt;  [5, 3] is also a valid answer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [-1,0]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [-1,0]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-3&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-3&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 3&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [0,1]&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [1,0]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;解題思路&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#解題思路&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 解題思路&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;solution&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#solution&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
